=============
* AWS Devops 
=============

# AWS DevOps Expert in 6 Months (6-8 Hours/Day Plan)  
*(Structured for maximum efficiency with hands-on projects, certifications, and job-ready skills)*  

## Month 1: AWS Fundamentals + Linux/Networking Refresher  
Goal: Master AWS basics, automation scripting, and core Linux/networking for DevOps.  

### Daily Breakdown (6-8 Hours)  
- Morning (3-4 hrs) → Theory + Labs  
- Afternoon (3-4 hrs) → Hands-On Projects  

+------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------+
| Week | Focus Area                       | Key AWS Services/Tools                 | Hands-On Lab/Project                       |
+------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------+
| 1    | AWS Core Services                | EC2, IAM, S3, VPC, CLI                 | Deploy a static website on S3 + CloudFront |
| 2    | Linux for DevOps (Advanced)      | Bash/Python scripting, Systemd, Logs   | Automate log cleanup + monitoring script 	|
| 3    | Networking Deep Dive             | Subnets, NACLs, Security Groups, ALB   | Build a 3-tier VPC with NAT Gateway 	|
| 4    | AWS Automation                   | AWS Lambda, EventBridge, SSM           | Automate EC2 backups with Lambda 		|
+------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------+--------------------------------------------+

### Month 1 Deliverables:
- Project 1: Fully automated EC2 deployment with user-data scripts  
- Project 2: Python script to fetch AWS resource metrics using Boto3  
- Cert Prep: AWS Cloud Practitioner (Optional but helpful)  

## Month 2: Infrastructure as Code (IaC) + CI/CD  
Goal: Master Terraform, AWS CloudFormation, and CI/CD pipelines.  

### Daily Breakdown  

+------+----------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| Week | Focus Area                       | Key Tools                               | Hands-On Lab/Project              |
+------+----------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 1    | Terraform (AWS)                  | Terraform modules, state management     | Deploy EKS cluster with Terraform |
| 2    | AWS CloudFormation               | YAML/JSON templates, StackSets          | Rebuild Terraform project in CFN 	|
| 3    | CI/CD Pipelines (AWS Native)     | AWS CodePipeline, CodeBuild, CodeDeploy | CI/CD for a Node.js app 		|
| 4    | Jenkins + GitHub Actions         | Jenkins on EC2, GitHub Actions for AWS  | Multi-branch pipeline 		|
+------+----------------------------------+-----------------------------------------+-----------------------------------+

### Month 2 Deliverables: 
- Project 3: Terraform-managed AWS infrastructure (VPC, EKS, RDS)  
- Project 4: Blue/Green deployment using CodeDeploy  
- Cert Prep: HashiCorp Terraform Associate (Optional)  

## Month 3: Containers & Kubernetes on AWS  
Goal: Master Docker, ECS, EKS, and Kubernetes operations.  

### Daily Breakdown  

+------+--------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| Week | Focus Area                     | Key Tools                                    | Hands-On Lab/Project             |
+------+--------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+
| 1    | Docker Deep Dive               | Dockerfiles, Compose, Security       	       | Dockerize a legacy app 	  |
| 2    | AWS ECS                        | Fargate, Task Definitions, Service Discovery | Deploy app on ECS 		  |
| 3    | AWS EKS                        | EKS clusters, Helm, Ingress (ALB)    	       | Deploy Prometheus+Grafana on EKS |
| 4    | Kubernetes Advanced            | HPA, RBAC, Network Policies         	       | Secure EKS cluster with OPA 	  |
+------+--------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+----------------------------------+

### Month 3 Deliverables:  
- Project 5: Microservices app on EKS with CI/CD  
- Project 6: Autoscaling EKS cluster with HPA  
- Cert Prep: AWS Certified DevOps Engineer - Pro (Start studying)  

## Month 4: DevSecOps + Observability  
Goal: Master security, monitoring, and chaos engineering.  

### Daily Breakdown 
 
+------+--------------------------+--------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+
| Week | Focus Area               | Key Tools                         	 | Hands-On Lab/Project                |
+------+--------------------------+--------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+
| 1    | AWS Security             | KMS, Secrets Manager, IAM Policies   | Encrypt EBS volumes + RDS           |
| 2    | Monitoring & Logging     | CloudWatch, Prometheus, Grafana      | Centralized logging with OpenSearch |
| 3    | Chaos Engineering        | AWS Fault Injection Simulator (FIS)  | Crash EKS pods + measure SLOs       |
| 4    | DevSecOps                | Trivy, Checkov, Aqua Security        | Secure CI/CD pipeline               |
+------+--------------------------+--------------------------------------+-------------------------------------+

### Month 4 Deliverables:  
- Project 7: Secure pipeline with SAST/DAST scans  
- Project 8: Chaos test on EKS cluster  
- Cert Prep: CKA (Certified Kubernetes Administrator)  

## Month 5: Advanced AWS DevOps + GitOps 
Goal: Master serverless, GitOps, and multi-account strategies.  

### Daily Breakdown

+------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------+------------------------------+  
| Week | Focus Area                       | Key Tools                          	   | Hands-On Lab/Project         |
+------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------+------------------------------+
| 1    | Serverless DevOps                | Lambda, Step Functions, SAM            | Serverless CI/CD pipeline 	  |
| 2    | GitOps (ArgoCD/FluxCD)           | ArgoCD on EKS, App of Apps pattern     | GitOps-managed EKS cluster   |
| 3    | Multi-Account AWS                | AWS Organizations, SCPs, Control Tower | Cross-account deployment     |
| 4    | Performance Optimization         | X-Ray, EKS tuning, RDS Proxy           | Optimize slow API with X-Ray |
+------+----------------------------------+----------------------------------------+------------------------------+

### Month 5 Deliverables:  
- Project 9: Serverless data pipeline (Lambda + DynamoDB)  
- Project 10: Multi-account Terraform deployment  
- Cert Prep: AWS DevOps Engineer - Pro (Exam readiness)  

## Month 6: Real-World Projects + Certifications  
Goal: Certifications, open-source contributions, and job readiness.  

### Daily Breakdown

+-------+----------------------------+------------------------------------------+
| Week  | Focus Area                 | **Key Activities**                     	|
+-------+----------------------------+------------------------------------------+
| 1-2   | Certification Exams        | AWS DevOps Pro, CKA, Terraform Associate |
|  3    | Open-Source Contribution   | Fix bugs in Terraform/AWS projects       |
|  4    | Resume & Interview Prep    | Mock interviews, DevOps case studies     |
+-------+----------------------------+------------------------------------------+

### Month 6 Deliverables: 
- Certified AWS DevOps Engineer - Professional  
- GitHub Portfolio (5+ advanced projects)  
- DevOps Interview Ready

# Key Tips for Maximum Results  
1. Build in Public – Share projects on LinkedIn/GitHub.  
2. AWS Free Tier – Use it wisely (shut down unused resources).  
3. Join AWS Communities – AWS Developers Slack, r/aws.  
4. Mock Exams – Use TDdojo, Whizlabs, and AWS Practice exams.  
